1. Project Description: What your site does and who it is for
This is an app that allows users to create and track personal workouts and optionally have a coach who can create and manage workout plans for them. 

2. Database Schema: An image of your entity relation diagram (ERD) exported from pgAdmin showing your tables and relationships


3. User Roles: Explanation of each role and what they can do
There are three roles: Admin, Coach, and Trainee

Trainee Can:
Create personal workouts
Edit/delete their workouts
Log workouts
Submit plan requests to Coach
View request status

Coach Can:
View workout plan requests from trainees
Create workouts for trainees
Edit workouts they created
Delete workouts they created
Add coaching notes to plan requests
View trainee workout progress
Update request status
Assign trainees to themselves
Remove coach–trainee assignments

Admin Can: 
Full system control
Manage users and roles (promote trainee to coach)
Delete any workout
View all workout logs
Manage plan requests


4. Test Account Credentials: Username or email for one account of each role type
Trainee: trainee@gmail.com
Coach: coach@gmail.com
Admin: admin@gmail.com


5. Known Limitations: Any features you did not complete or bugs you are aware of


================================
Notes for self : Project Roadmap 

* Completed steps have '-' at beginning *

Phase 1 — Finalize the System Design
Tasks:
-Confirm the user roles
-Confirm the features each role has
-Decide what core entities exist (users, workouts, logs, requests, etc.)



Phase 2 — Database Design 
Tasks:
-List the tables you need.
-Decide the columns for each table.
-define primary keys
-define foreign keys
-determine relationships.
Create the ERD diagram in pgAdmin.


Phase 3 — Project Setup
Tasks:
-initialize Node project
-install Express
-install EJS
-configure ESM
-create/update folder structure (MVC)
-start the server
-test that a page renders


Phase 4 — PostgreSQL Connection
Connect the app to database.
Tasks:
-install pg
-create connection pool
-test a query
-verify database connection


Phase 5 — Authentication System
Tasks:
-login and register form views
-register route
-password hashing with bcrypt
-login route
-logout route
-session management with express-session


Phase 6 — Authorization (Roles)
After authentication works, add role protection.
Tasks:
-build protected dashboard
middleware for isAuthenticated
middleware for isCoach
middleware for isAdmin
protect routes


Phase 7 — Core Feature: Workouts
Implement the main content system.
Tasks:
create workout
edit workout
delete workout
view workouts


Phase 8 — Workout Logging
Add the progress tracking feature.
Tasks:
log workout
edit log
delete log
view logs


Phase 9 — Workflow System
Implement the required multi-stage workflow.
Tasks:
submit workout plan request
coach views requests
coach updates request status
coach adds notes


Phase 10 — Admin Dashboard
Implement admin control.
Tasks:
manage users
change user roles
view all workouts
delete inappropriate workouts


Phase 11 — Validation and Security
Improve robustness.
Tasks:
validate form inputs
sanitize input
parameterized SQL queries
error handling middleware
requirements pass (parameterized SQL, express-validator, global error handler)


Phase 12 — Deployment
Final step!
Tasks:
push project to GitHub
deploy to Render
connect PostgreSQL database
configure environment variables
